{
 "name": "RPlog_Good_Old-Fashioned_Business",
 "title": "Good Old-Fashioned Business",
 "summary": "In the notorious Meltdown Cafe on Nar Shaddaa, the stiff, ex-Imperial agent Zeak Oppenhiemer seeks out the one-handed smuggler Jaspar Andromidas to broker a job on behalf of the Etti group. The deal: run food and medical supplies to Caspar, sell them openly while loudly crediting the Etti group at every turn, then buy non-essential goods for Bonadan with the proceeds. Wary at first -- having already lost a hand to the Imperials on a previous Caspar run -- Jaspar haggles over the fee, eventually settling on two thousand credits up front and two on delivery, plus a Caspian living allowance. When Jaspar's blacklisted ship and identity prove a complication, Zeak offers to loan him one of his volatile wife's 'toys' -- the Padawan Johanna Siri te Danaan's vessel -- provided it is returned intact. The two seal a cordial business arrangement, and Zeak abruptly departs to recruit other pilots.",
